sections.Biography:
Aenys was the firstborn son of [[Aegon I Targaryen|Aegon the Conqueror]], by Aegon's sister-wife Queen [[Rhaenys Targaryen (sister of Aegon I)|Rhaenys Targaryen]]. After his father died, Aenys succeeded as the second King on the [[Iron Throne]]. Despite the fact that Aenys had a son, [[Jaehaerys I Targaryen|Jaehaerys]], when he died he was succeeded by his half-brother [[Maegor Targaryen]], known as &quot;Maegor the Cruel&quot;. Maegor was the son of Aegon's other sister-wife, Queen [[Visenya Targaryen]]. Maegor ultimately died childless, however, and Aenys's son succeeded to the throne as King Jaehaerys I. As a result all subsequent Targaryen monarchs descend from Aenys, not Maegor.

===[[Season 1]]===
Aenys's name is briefly seen on a page of the book &quot;[[The Lineages and Histories of the Great Houses of the Seven Kingdoms]]&quot; when Lord [[Eddard Stark]] is searching through it. On a page about [[House Baratheon]], it is mentioned that [[Raymont Baratheon|one]] of [[Orys Baratheon]]'s sons died thwarting an assassination attempt against Aenys.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[A Golden Crown]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
